article.description: — Tyreke Key had 18 points as Indiana State beat Southeast Missouri 72-66 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Key, LaRavia carry Indiana State over SE Missouri 72-66
article.linkText: Key, LaRavia carry Indiana State over SE Missouri 72-66
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- — Tyreke Key had 18 points as Indiana State beat Southeast Missouri 72-66 on Tuesday. Jake LaRavia added 15 points for the Sycamores (3-2), and Tre Williams chipped in 11 points. Chris Harris had 16 points and six rebounds for the Redhawks (2-5), whose losing streak stretched to four games. Dylan Branson added 12 points and Nolan Taylor had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
